<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[801,1451,652,900]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis box="[839,898,653,676]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Notes</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[937,1178,653,676]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="portoricensis">
<emphasis box="[937,1178,653,676]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Scapania portoricensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only neotropical member of the large, holarctic genus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dumort.) Dumort." authorityName="Dumort." baseAuthorityName="Dumort." class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1227,1323,685,708]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Scapania</emphasis>
(Dumort.) Dumort.
</taxonomicName>
and characteristic of upper montane cloud forests (FRAHM &amp; GRADSTEIN, 1991). The species is readily recognized by its reddish color, large size (to 
<quantity box="[1276,1345,780,804]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[801,853,812,836]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
wide), toothed leaf margins, very short keel and stellate gemmae. 
<taxonomicName box="[955,1174,844,868]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="minutidens">
<emphasis box="[955,1174,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Scapania minutidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a robust phenotype of 
<emphasis box="[801,958,877,900]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName box="[801,954,877,900]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="portoricensis">S. portoricensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
